					<description><![CDATA[<p>Scratch writing from scratch with these templates for outreach, welcome, thank you, announcement, and customer appreciation emails.</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/03/30/business-email-templates">5 Copy &#038; Paste Email Templates Any Business Can Use</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.wordstream.com">WordStream</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Fact: Email marketing returns <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2017/06/29/email-marketing-statistics">$40</a> for every $1 spent. It&#8217;s no wonder it&#8217;s one of the top marketing channels in terms of ROI.</p>
<p><img fetchpriority="high" decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/email-marketing-ROI.png" alt="ROI of marketing channels" width="720" height="450" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-59525" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/email-marketing-ROI.png 720w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/email-marketing-ROI-480x300.png 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 720px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>But whether you‚Äôre prospecting, onboarding new users, saying thanks, or making a big announcement, staring at your cursor in a blank email is where all too many of us find ourselves. Luckily, you don‚Äôt have to reinvent the wheel. Because in this post, we&#8217;ve got five email templates you can use to get your communication off to a great start.</p>
<p><strong>Table of contents</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><a href="#welcome">Onboarding/welcome email</a></li>
<li><a href="#outreach">Cold outreach email</a></li>
<li><a href="#thankyou">Thank you email</a></li>
<li><a href="#announcement">Announcement email</a></li>
<li><a href="#appreciation">Customer appreciation email</a><a href="#announcement"></a></li>
</ul>
<h2>Tips for using email templates</h2>
<p>Email templates help to save you time, minimize typos, and keep your branding consistent, but there is a right and a wrong way to use them. Be sure to follow these tips when using email templates</p>
<ol>
<li><strong>Customize them: </strong>Templates should only serve as the base of your email. They should be customized to include specific details about your recipient so that they&#8217;re genuine. No point in saving time if your emails don&#8217;t make your customers feel valued.</li>
<li><strong>Double-check them: </strong>Even though templates can reduce errors, you still need to check and double-check them before sending‚Äîespecially because if you&#8217;re following tip one, you will be manipulating the content.</li>
<li><strong>Test them: </strong>Templates can reduce your workload, but that doesn&#8217;t mean you&#8217;re off the hook with testing your emails. You should still try out different versions of the same template to see which one performs better, and even periodically change up your templates to keep them from going stale.</li>
<li><strong>Set them up in your email platform: </strong>Once you have the copy that works, don&#8217;t just save the copy to your notepad. <a href="https://www.rightinbox.com/blog/how-to-set-up-email-templates-in-gmail" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Set up Gmail templates</a> to have them at the ready.</li>
<li><strong>Use design templates too:¬†</strong>The templates below can be used as Gmail templates, but a branded HTML email offers a more attractive and professional touch. There are a number of branded email templates out there to choose from as well.</li>
</ol>
<div class='et-box et-shadow'>
					<div class='et-box-content'><p><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/1f4eb.png" alt="üì´" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /><strong> (Lots) more free email templates</strong>¬†¬†<strong>&gt;&gt; </strong><a href="https://marketing.wordstream.com/WSLIQContentDLWebsiteEmailExampleTemplate.html?cid=Web_Any_InContentTextLink_Email_EmailTemplates_Download">30 Free Small Business Email Examples &amp; Templates</a></p></div></div>
<h2>5 must-have email templates for business</h2>
<p>Use these templates as a starting point for your emails‚Äîbut remember to adjust them to your <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2014/07/31/brand-voice">brand voice</a> and as always,<a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2021/04/08/write-emails-like-a-human"> write like a human being</a>!<br />
<a id="welcome"></a></p>
<h3>1. Customer welcome/onboarding email template</h3>
<p>Here‚Äôs an email template you can use for introducing new customers to your business after they‚Äôve registered, made a purchase, or subscribed to your product.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/welcome-email-template-for-business.png" alt="welcome email template for business" width="689" height="520" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-59481" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/welcome-email-template-for-business.png 689w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/welcome-email-template-for-business-480x362.png 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 689px, 100vw" /></p>
<p><strong>Subject line: Welcome to {business name}!</strong></p>
<p><em>Hey {customer‚Äôs name}, </em></p>
<p><em>Thanks so much for joining us at {your company name}! We‚Äôre excited to have you join our {team, family, etc.}, and we think you‚Äôll really love {product, feature, etc.}. If you haven‚Äôt already, make sure to check out: </em></p>
<ul>
<li><em> {feature 1}</em></li>
<li><em> {feature 2}</em></li>
<li><em> {feature 3}</em></li>
</ul>
<p><em>Don‚Äôt hesitate to drop us a line if you have any questions or need any help. We‚Äôre open from {hours}, and you can reach us {at/by} {contact info}. And don‚Äôt forget to look at our FAQ page if you need help outside of our regular business hours. </em></p>
<p><em> Thanks again and happy to have you!</em></p>
<p><em> Best,</em></p>
<p><em>{your name}</em></p>
<h3>Welcome email tips</h3>
<ul>
<li>Follow our advice for <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2014/08/05/increase-email-signups">getting more email signups</a> and use <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2021/02/11/call-to-action-examples-for-email-newsletter-signups">creative newsletter signup CTAs</a> so you can have more welcome emails to send.</li>
<li>Get the reader excited about their decision and make their next steps clear&#8230;.</li>
<li>&#8230;but don&#8217;t overwhelm them. Share the basics and then link to external resources.</li>
<li>Learn more in our <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2017/08/18/welcome-email">welcome email tips</a>.<a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2017/08/18/welcome-email"></a></li>
</ul>
<p><a id="outreach"></a></p>
<h3>2. Sales outreach email template</h3>
<p><a href="https://mailshake.com/blog/outreach-templates/">Cold outreach sales campaigns</a> can be tricky, but effective if you do it right. Here&#8217;s a template to point you in the right direction</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/cold-outreach-email-template-business.png" alt="outreach email template for business" width="700" height="520" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-59484" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/cold-outreach-email-template-business.png 700w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/cold-outreach-email-template-business-480x357.png 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 700px, 100vw" /></p>
<p><strong><em>Subject line: A faster way to {achieve goal}</em></strong></p>
<p><em>Hey {prospect‚Äôs name},</em></p>
<p><em>I saw that you‚Äôre working on {prospect‚Äôs initiative}, and {compliment}. My name is {your name}, and I work at {your company name}, where we help people like you achieve their goals with the help of {product}. </em></p>
<p><em>I know you‚Äôre busy, so here are a few quick features that I think you might find useful:</em></p>
<ul>
<li><em> {feature 1}</em></li>
<li><em> {feature 2}</em></li>
<li><em> {feature 3}</em></li>
</ul>
<p><em>I‚Äôd be happy to go over everything in more detail if you‚Äôre interested. You can schedule an appointment with me through my {calendar program}. </em></p>
<p><em>Looking forward to hearing from you!</em></p>
<p><em>-{your name}</em></p>
<h3>Cold outreach email tips</h3>
<ul>
<li>Don‚Äôt be too aggressive. The tone should be that of inviting the reader to an opportunity, not pushing them to a decision.</li>
<li>Respect your reader&#8217;s time. Keep it brief and make it easy for the prospect to find the most important information.</li>
<li>Say something specific about your prospect and their problem.</li>
<li>Follow my steps to <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2018/12/03/cold-email">grow your business with cold email</a>.</li>
</ul>
<p><a id="thankyou"></a></p>
<h3>3. Thank you email template</h3>
<p>Here‚Äôs an email template you can use to <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/07/07/thank-you-for-your-order-messages">thank customers for their purchase</a> or for signing up for a list or service. Just edit it to fit the situation.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/thank-you-email-template-for-business.png" alt="thank you email template for business" width="717" height="437" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-59479" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/thank-you-email-template-for-business.png 717w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/thank-you-email-template-for-business-480x293.png 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 717px, 100vw" /></p>
<p><strong><em>Subject line: Thank you! (Coupon inside)</em></strong></p>
<p><em>Hey {name},</em></p>
<p><em>Thanks so much for {action the customer took}. We‚Äôre positive that you‚Äôre going to enjoy {product} as much as we do.</em></p>
<p><em>As an extra thank you, here‚Äôs {promotion, coupon, etc.} for your next {action}.</em></p>
<p>Also, don‚Äôt forget to check out {other product}. If you like {current product}, we think you‚Äôll love {other product} just as much.</p>
<p><em>Thanks again,</em></p>
<p><em>{your name}</em></p>
<h3>Thank you email tips:</h3>
<ul>
<li>A thank you email should be gracious but doesn‚Äôt need to be particularly long.</li>
<li>Don&#8217;t make it a goodbye. This is a great opportunity to offer a discount on their next order or even an <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2018/05/30/cross-selling-upselling">upsell</a>.</li>
<li>Use our <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2021/11/23/thank-you-page-examples">thank you page examples</a> for added inspiration.</li>
</ul>
<p><a id="announcement"></a></p>
<h3>4. Announcement email template</h3>
<p>Announcement emails are a bit harder to use a template for since the structure dependends on what you‚Äôre announcing, but here‚Äôs an idea to help get you started.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/announcement-email-template-for-business.png" alt="announcement email template for business" width="648" height="509" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-59478" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/announcement-email-template-for-business.png 648w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/announcement-email-template-for-business-480x377.png 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 648px, 100vw" /></p>
<p><strong><em>Subject line: It&#8217;s here! {product, event, feature, etc}</em></strong></p>
<p><em>Hey {name}, </em></p>
<p><em>We‚Äôre incredibly excited to announce {event}! After a lot of work, we‚Äôre finally ready to bring {product, location, etc.} to the world, and we‚Äôre hoping that you‚Äôll enjoy using it just as much as we have working on it. </em></p>
<p><em>Here are a few reasons that we‚Äôre excited about {product, event, etc.}:</em></p>
<ul>
<li><em> {reason 1}</em></li>
<li><em> {reason 2}</em></li>
<li><em> {reason 3}</em></li>
</ul>
<p><em>But enough talking, why not give it a try for yourself? You can {action} by heading over to {website, location}. Plus, since you‚Äôre already on our email list, we‚Äôll give you {discount, perk, etc.}. </em></p>
<p><em>If you‚Äôve got any questions, feel free to reach out to us at {contact info}. </em></p>
<p><em>Thanks again for being here on this journey with us. </em></p>
<p><em>Best,</em></p>
<p><em>{your name}</em></p>
<h3>Announcement email tips</h3>
<ul>
<li>Don&#8217;t be afraid to celebrate the hard work that went into getting the feature, product, or event live.</li>
<li>Consider giving your loyal customers early access.</li>
<li>Make sure that what you‚Äôre announcing is worthy of an email and relevant to your customers.</li>
<li>Give your readers an action to complete to get involved.</li>
</ul>
<p><a id="appreciation"></a></p>
<h3>5. Customer appreciation email template</h3>
<p>This email template can be used</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/customer-appreciation-email-template-for-business.png" alt="customer appreciation email template for business" width="720" height="438" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-59477" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/customer-appreciation-email-template-for-business.png 720w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/customer-appreciation-email-template-for-business-480x292.png 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 720px, 100vw" /></p>
<p><strong><em>Subject line: A special gift for our loyal customers</em></strong></p>
<p><em>Hey {name},</em></p>
<p><em>This month, we celebrate our nth year in business! Sure, we love {your trade} but what really keeps us going is customers like you. As our way of saying thanks, we&#8217;re offering {promotion} all month long.</em></p>
<p><em>This deal isn&#8217;t for everyone‚Äîonly our most loyal customers‚Äîand it&#8217;ll be gone before you know it!</em></p>
<p><em>Call us to book your appointment today, and mention promo code {promo code}.</em></p>
<p><em>See you soon!</em></p>
<p><em>-{your name}</em></p>
<h3>Customer appreciation email tips</h3>
<ul>
<li>Avoid using the term &#8220;valued customers&#8221;‚Äîit&#8217;s empty and a great way to show you don&#8217;t value them.</li>
<li>Take a gander through these <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/customer-appreciation-ideas/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">low-cost, high-value customer appreciation ideas</a>.</li>
<li>Find more examples and templates with our <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/02/04/valentines-day-messages-clients">Valentine&#8217;s Day customer appreciation emails</a> and <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2021/11/29/holiday-customer-appreciation-letter">holiday customer appreciation emails</a>.</li>
</ul>
